# Roadmap-driven execution (AION)

## Single source of truth (no parallel trackers)

- **Repository JSON:** `src/content/ecosystem-status.json`, `src/content/roadmap-subsystem-extensions.json`, `src/content/roadmap-execution.json`, `src/content/releases.json`.
- **Merge:** `getEcosystemStatus()` in `src/lib/ecosystem-data.ts` (extensions + execution bundle + optional Supabase).
- **Cloud overlay:** `ecosystem_public_snapshots` kinds `portal_ecosystem`, `portal_roadmap_master` — see `src/lib/ecosystem/cloud-queries.ts`.
- **Machine-readable:** `GET /api/aion/context` (includes `executionEngine`), `GET /api/roadmap/execution`, plus slice APIs listed on `/ai-context`.
- **Human pages:** `/roadmap/execution`, `/operations/context`, `/control`, `/operations`, `/status`, `/roadmap`.

## Cursor MUST NOT

- Randomly switch subsystems or epics without an explicit user rescope (follow `executionQueue` + `execution.activeEpics`).
- Mark `fully_done` without `definitionOfDone` + `releaseQualityBar` alignment and real code verification.
- Add placeholder UX in user-visible flows (disabled + copy, or hide).
- Create disconnected UI (screens without data contract / API).
- Duplicate backend or merge logic (extend `ecosystem-data`, `payload-guards`, existing repos).
- Invent readiness %, blockers, or debt without observable evidence.

## Cursor SHOULD (within roadmap priorities)

- Read `/api/roadmap/execution` or `executionEngine` in `/api/aion/context` before large changes.
- Improve weak UX and consistency when it advances `executionQueue.nextImplementationTarget` or the focused subsystem.
- Strengthen realtime/cloud/release paths when aligned with `aiExecutionNotes` and epics.
- Ask the user to consult **ChatGPT** for architecture/spec when ambiguity remains after reading JSON SoT.

## ChatGPT vs Cursor (collaboration)

- **ChatGPT:** architecture, tradeoffs, ecosystem review, sequencing — use when design is unclear.
- **Cursor:** implementation, integration, refactor — execute against the JSON queue and Zod-valid payloads.

## When editing roadmap data

- Bump `lastUpdated` in `ecosystem-status.json` when subsystem/execution meaningfully changes.
- Keep `technicalDebt[].evidence` concrete (file, table, scenario).
- Update `roadmap-execution.json` **executionQueue** when the true next target or blockers change.
